ything? From the dawn of creation, the Wild God, the Great Yogi, the sum of all opposites, has been guardian of the absolute. By retelling and interweaving the many myths that keep Siva alive in India today, Kramrisch reveals the paradoxes in Siva's nature and thus in the nature of consciousness itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mrz 2021) 0aCave templeszIndiazElephanta Island. 0aHindu sculpturezIndiazElephanta Island. 0aHindu sculpturezIndiazEllora Caves. 7aRELIGION / Buddhism / General (see also PHILOSOPHY / Buddhist).2bisacsh  a"Rudra, Wild Hunter.  aActa Orientalia.  aAdbhuta.  aAmśumal.  aAnasūyā.  aAnthropos.  aArdhanārīśvara.  aArtibus Asiae.  aBhagīratha.  aBhairava.  aBudha.  aDakṣiṇāmūrti.  aEkavrātya.  aFulfiller of the sacrifice.  aGaṅgā.  aGaṇapati.  aHanumān.  aHarvard Oriental Series.  aHarvard Theological Review.  aHiraṇyagarbha.  aHistory of Religions.  aIndian Antiquary.  aIndian Culture.  aIndian Historical Quarterly.  aJalandhara.  aJournal of Indian History.  aKaivalya.  aKing of the sacrifice.  aKāla, a form of Śarva.  aKālanemi.  aKāmalākṣa.  aKāvyamālā.  aKīrttimukha.  aKṛśānu's arrow.  aLakulin.  aMahādeva.  aMandara.  aMaya.  aPitāmaha.  aPrajāpati, the sacrifice.  aPrajāpati, the year.  aRudra as Kirāta.  aRudra's primordial shot.  aSacred Books of the Hindus.  aThe boar of heaven.  aTrivandrum Sanskrit Series.  aahaṃkāra.  abodhicitta.  abrahman.  apralaya".  aserpents.  aūrdhvaliṅga.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton eBook Package Archive 1931-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691224220zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691224220423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691224220.jp